Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a big pinch
of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice
is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 4.

== Pico de Gallo ==

While rice cooks, dice @Roma Tomato{1}(diced). Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%oz}(roughly chopped).
Halve, peel, and finely chop @Yellow Onion{1}(halved, peeled, finely chopped).
Mince @Jalapeño{1}(minced), removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Zest and quarter
@Lime{1}(zested and quartered).

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, cilantro, 2 TBSP onion (4 TBSP for 4 servings),
half the jalapeño, and a squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{2%tbsp} with a squeeze of lime
juice. Season with salt and pepper. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches
a drizzling consistency.

== Black Bean Filling ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add remaining onion and remaining jalapeño. Season with a pinch of @salt{}.
Cook until browned and softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @Black Beans{13.4%oz} and their liquid, @Mushroom Stock Concentrate{1},
@Southwest Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, salt (we used ½ tsp; 1 tsp salt for 4 servings),
and pepper. Bring to a simmer and cook until liquid has reduced, ~{5-7%minutes}.
Remove from heat.

== Rice ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} and lime zest to taste. Season
with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Using your hands, break half the @Blue Corn Tortilla Chips{1.5%oz} into bite-size
pieces over a #medium bowl{} (keep the rest whole for serving).

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave until warm and pliable,
~{30%seconds}.

Lay tortillas on a clean work surface. Place 1⁄3 cup rice in a line on the bottom
third of each tortilla. Top with ½ cup bean mixture (you'll have some rice and
beans left over—save for serving); sprinkle with @Mexican Cheese Blend{1/4%cup}.
Top with crema, pico de gallo, and crushed tortilla chips.

Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right
sides toward the filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form
burritos.

> TIP: For less mess, place each tortilla on a large piece of aluminum foil or
> parchment paper, then wrap up with foil or paper. Simply unwrap as you eat!

Halve burritos.

Divide burritos and remaining rice, bean mixture, lime crema, pico de gallo, and
tortilla chips between plates. Serve with @Hot Sauce{1%tsp} and any remaining
lime wedges on the side.